WEBVTT

1
00:00:45.128 --> 00:00:48.335
<i>This is a story from long ago,</i>

2
00:00:48.408 --> 00:00:51.855
<i>when the great mammoths
still roamed our lands.</i>

3
00:00:54.286 --> 00:00:57.373
<i>It's the story
of my two brothers and me.</i>

4
00:00:57.925 --> 00:00:59.724
<i>When the three of us were young,</i>

5
00:00:59.804 --> 00:01:03.327
<i>we were taught
that the world is full of magic.</i>

6
00:01:08.482 --> 00:01:12.161
<i>The source of this magic
is the ever-changing lights</i>

7
00:01:12.196 --> 00:01:14.321
<i>that dance across the sky.</i>

8
00:01:17.839 --> 00:01:19.643
<i>The shaman woman of our village</i>

9
00:01:19.678 --> 00:01:23.561
<i>told us that these lights
are the spirits of our ancestors,</i>

10
00:01:23.638 --> 00:01:28.001
<i>and that they have the power
to make changes in our world.</i>

11
00:01:31.436 --> 00:01:33.955
<i>Small things become big.</i>

12
00:01:36.314 --> 00:01:38.397
<i>Winter turns to spring.</i>

13
00:01:41.512 --> 00:01:44.959
<i>One thing always changes
into another.</i>

14
00:01:46.871 --> 00:01:49.991
<i>But the greatest change I ever saw</i>

15
00:01:50.070 --> 00:01:51.870
<i>was that of my brother,</i>

16
00:01:52.469 --> 00:01:57.269
<i>a boy who desperately
wanted to be a man.</i>

17
00:02:00.307 --> 00:02:02.391
- Get down.
- What?

18
00:02:02.707 --> 00:02:04.594
Get down! Get down!

19
00:02:11.185 --> 00:02:12.548
Kenai.

20
00:02:32.059 --> 00:02:34.067
Never try to milk a caribou.

21
00:02:38.376 --> 00:02:41.776
No. No, don't. No. Come on, don't. No.

22
00:02:41.811 --> 00:02:44.143
Hey. Will you two knock it off?

23
00:02:44.615 --> 00:02:47.694
That's all right.
After today, he won't treat me like that.

24
00:02:47.729 --> 00:02:50.737
Oh, right, the big manhood ceremony.

25
00:02:51.133 --> 00:02:54.460
Doesn't matter what the spirits say,
you'll always be our baby brother.

26
00:02:54.533 --> 00:02:57.293
- Well, wait till I get my totem.
- Baby brother.

27
00:02:58.811 --> 00:03:00.938
Hey, I said knock it off.

28
00:03:01.010 --> 00:03:04.130
The quicker we get these fish,
the faster we get to your ceremony.

29
00:03:04.210 --> 00:03:07.969
Let's all just try and get along
for a few hours. Okay, Denahi?

30
00:03:08.004 --> 00:03:10.208
- Whatever you say.
- Okay, Ken...

31
00:03:10.243 --> 00:03:12.488
So, what are we waiting for?

32
00:03:18.285 --> 00:03:21.449
- Whoo!
- Whoo!

33
00:03:21.605 --> 00:03:26.372
<i>When the Earth was young
and the air was sweet</i>

34
00:03:26.723 --> 00:03:31.010
<i>And the mountains kissed the sky</i>

35
00:03:32.281 --> 00:03:34.921
<i>In the great beyond</i>

36
00:03:35.001 --> 00:03:37.245
<i>With its many paths</i>

37
00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:41.088
<i>Man and nature lived side by side</i>

38
00:03:42.839 --> 00:03:46.885
<i>In this wilderness of danger and beauty</i>

39
00:03:47.998 --> 00:03:51.957
<i>Lived three brothers bonded by love</i>

40
00:03:53.756 --> 00:03:56.604
<i>Their hearts full of joy</i>

41
00:03:56.675 --> 00:03:58.998
<i>They ask now for guidance</i>

42
00:03:59.074 --> 00:04:03.241
<i>Reaching out to the skies up above</i>

43
00:04:04.393 --> 00:04:07.351
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

44
00:04:07.386 --> 00:04:10.035
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

45
00:04:10.111 --> 00:04:14.310
<i>Fill our hearts and souls
with all you know</i>

46
00:04:15.469 --> 00:04:18.033
<i>Show us that in your eyes</i>

47
00:04:18.109 --> 00:04:20.117
<i>We are all the same</i>

48
00:04:20.788 --> 00:04:25.228
<i>Brothers to each other
in this world we remain</i>

49
00:04:25.827 --> 00:04:28.194
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

50
00:04:28.266 --> 00:04:32.270
<i>Give us wisdom to pass to each other</i>

51
00:04:33.505 --> 00:04:37.225
<i>And give us strength so we understand</i>

52
00:04:39.223 --> 00:04:41.684
<i>That the things we do</i>

53
00:04:41.719 --> 00:04:44.145
<i>The choices we make</i>

54
00:04:44.222 --> 00:04:47.909
<i>Give direction to all life's plans</i>

55
00:04:49.700 --> 00:04:54.021
<i>To look and wonder
at all we've been given</i>

56
00:04:54.899 --> 00:04:59.066
<i>In a world that's not always as it seems</i>

57
00:05:00.617 --> 00:05:03.224
<i>Every corner we turn</i>

58
00:05:03.296 --> 00:05:05.740
<i>Only leads to another</i>

59
00:05:05.816 --> 00:05:10.015
<i>A journey ends but another begins</i>

60
00:05:11.294 --> 00:05:14.261
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

61
00:05:14.333 --> 00:05:16.897
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

62
00:05:16.973 --> 00:05:21.052
<i>Fill our hearts and souls
with all you know</i>

63
00:05:22.331 --> 00:05:24.938
<i>Show us that in your eyes</i>

64
00:05:25.010 --> 00:05:26.930
<i>We are all the same</i>

65
00:05:27.690 --> 00:05:32.250
<i>Brothers to each other
in this world we remain</i>

66
00:05:32.728 --> 00:05:34.769
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

67
00:05:34.967 --> 00:05:37.247
- Kenai's back.
- Kenai.

68
00:05:37.327 --> 00:05:40.773
Kenai, are you excited
about getting your spirit rock today?

69
00:05:41.086 --> 00:05:43.965
It's not a rock. It'll be my totem.

70
00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:45.132
Ooh!

71
00:05:45.205 --> 00:05:48.325
I'll probably get a sabre-tooth tiger
for bravery,

72
00:05:48.403 --> 00:05:50.288
or strength, or greatness.

73
00:05:50.323 --> 00:05:53.726
- Something that fits me.
- A mammoth for your fat head?

74
00:05:53.802 --> 00:05:56.725
- Make sure you get that basket tied up.
- Don't worry.

75
00:05:56.801 --> 00:05:59.281
No stupid bear
is gonna get near this fish.

76
00:05:59.316 --> 00:06:03.200
Just tie it up.

77
00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:06.683
- She's back. Tanana's back.
- Come on.

78
00:06:07.958 --> 00:06:10.206
- Come on, Kenai, let's go.
- Come on.

79
00:06:10.278 --> 00:06:12.438
Tanana's got your rock.
Come on.

80
00:06:18.475 --> 00:06:21.518
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

81
00:06:21.594 --> 00:06:23.797
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

82
