86
00:06:39.630 --> 00:06:42.510
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

87
00:06:42.588 --> 00:06:47.268
<i>Brothers all the same</i>

88
00:06:48.027 --> 00:06:49.192
Nana.

89
00:06:49.227 --> 00:06:53.710
- Hey, Nana.
- Well, hello there, sweetheart.

90
00:06:53.786 --> 00:06:56.066
What a big girl.

91
00:06:58.224 --> 00:07:03.831
When each of us comes of age,
the great spirits reveal to us a totem

92
00:07:03.903 --> 00:07:06.663
that helps guide us through our lives.

93
00:07:07.462 --> 00:07:10.145
Some of us use courage to guide us.

94
00:07:11.380 --> 00:07:13.060
Others patience.

95
00:07:15.300 --> 00:07:17.907
And some of us beauty.

96
00:07:20.898 --> 00:07:22.142
Kenai.

97
00:07:24.737 --> 00:07:27.181
- You nervous?
- Excited.

98
00:07:27.456 --> 00:07:30.183
You should be.
It's a good one.

99
00:07:30.975 --> 00:07:35.502
Kenai, I have been to the mountain
where the lights touch the earth,

100
00:07:35.574 --> 00:07:40.177
and the great spirits
have revealed to me your totem.

101
00:07:40.933 --> 00:07:46.572
To become a man, your actions
must be guided by one thing.

102
00:07:47.970 --> 00:07:51.177
Your totem is...

103
00:07:54.128 --> 00:07:55.416
Love.

104
00:07:56.448 --> 00:07:59.416
- What?
- Yes, love.

105
00:08:00.487 --> 00:08:02.411
The bear of love?

106
00:08:02.446 --> 00:08:06.810
A love that connects
and unites all living things.

107
00:08:06.885 --> 00:08:09.732
- Who wants to trade?
- There is no trading.

108
00:08:10.524 --> 00:08:12.368
Oh, Kenai,

109
00:08:12.803 --> 00:08:15.290
love is the most precious of totems.

110
00:08:15.363 --> 00:08:18.450
It reveals itself in unexpected ways.

111
00:08:19.121 --> 00:08:23.724
Let love guide your actions,
then one day you'll be a man,

112
00:08:24.320 --> 00:08:28.967
and we'll place your mark
next to those of our ancestors.

113
00:08:45.314 --> 00:08:46.754
Oh.

114
00:08:51.312 --> 00:08:53.396
There he is.

115
00:08:53.472 --> 00:08:55.632
Come here, lover boy.

116
00:08:55.711 --> 00:08:58.275
- Leave me alone.
- Kenai, wait.

117
00:08:59.231 --> 00:09:01.475
- I'm sorry.
- What?

118
00:09:01.510 --> 00:09:04.034
Your totem, I think it's really great.

119
00:09:04.069 --> 00:09:06.748
- You do?
- Yeah. And I made you something.

120
00:09:06.783 --> 00:09:07.992
Really?

121
00:09:08.027 --> 00:09:10.787
Now when you skip around
loving everybody,

122
00:09:10.822 --> 00:09:13.351
you'll smell so sweet.

123
00:09:13.426 --> 00:09:15.226
Well, isn't this nice?

124
00:09:15.306 --> 00:09:17.590
Instead of fighting,
you're giving each other flowers.

125
00:09:17.625 --> 00:09:21.312
Yeah, isn't it lovely?
He's so in touch with his totem already.

126
00:09:21.784 --> 00:09:24.543
Hey, dog breath,
go take care of the fish.

127
00:09:24.578 --> 00:09:27.548
Sure. Kenai loves me, he loves me not.

128
00:09:27.583 --> 00:09:31.303
Kenai loves me, he loves me not.
Kenai loves me, he loves...

129
00:09:31.381 --> 00:09:35.069
- Kenai.
- Someday I'm gonna just...

130
00:09:35.580 --> 00:09:37.707
- He's just such a...
- Hey, bonehead.

131
00:09:37.779 --> 00:09:40.822
Just because his totem is wisdom
doesn't mean he's wise.

132
00:09:40.899 --> 00:09:44.063
- I mean, look at him.
- Kenai loves me, he loves me not.

133
00:09:44.377 --> 00:09:46.418
- Hi, Denahi.
- Oh, hi.

134
00:09:46.818 --> 00:09:49.141
Let go!

135
00:09:49.176 --> 00:09:52.055
Yeah, the spirits messed up
on both of our totems.

136
00:09:52.090 --> 00:09:54.455
I felt the same way
when Tanana gave me mine.

137
00:09:54.535 --> 00:09:56.340
- Get out of here.
- No, really.

138
00:09:56.375 --> 00:10:00.334
I said, "The eagle of guidance?
What does that mean?"

139
00:10:00.413 --> 00:10:03.213
But now that I'm older,
I know it's about being a leader

140
00:10:03.248 --> 00:10:04.980
and keeping an eye on you two.

141
00:10:07.131 --> 00:10:09.498
I just want to get my handprint
on that wall.

142
00:10:09.571 --> 00:10:13.969
Just be patient, Kenai.
When you live by your totem, you will.

143
00:10:14.004 --> 00:10:16.009
- Really?
- Guarantee it.

144
00:10:18.968 --> 00:10:22.328
But come on, the bear of love?

145
00:10:22.407 --> 00:10:24.452
I mean, a bear doesn't love anyone.

146
00:10:24.487 --> 00:10:27.367
They don't think. They don't feel.
I mean, they're...

147
00:10:29.485 --> 00:10:32.452
- They're thieves.
- You didn't tie it up, did you?

148
00:10:32.524 --> 00:10:33.528
Uh...

149
00:10:33.604 --> 00:10:35.243
You should get the totem of pinheads.

150
00:10:35.278 --> 00:10:36.448
Knock it off.

151
00:10:36.483 --> 00:10:38.527
- We'll just make another basket.
- We?

152
00:10:38.562 --> 00:10:42.043
Oh, no. It took me two weeks
to make that basket.

153
00:10:42.602 --> 00:10:45.920
Get lover boy to do it.
He's the one always messing things up.

154
00:10:45.955 --> 00:10:49.084
- Typical Kenai.
- All right, I'll go get your basket.

155
00:10:49.600 --> 00:10:52.000
Kenai, wait. Kenai!

156
00:10:54.638 --> 00:10:56.166
What?

157
00:11:16.672 --> 00:11:19.672
Kenai!

158
00:11:20.631 --> 00:11:22.235
Kenai!

159
00:11:22.270 --> 00:11:25.237
- Where'd he go?
- If we're lucky, far away.

160
00:11:29.588 --> 00:11:30.832
Kenai!

161
00:11:33.987 --> 00:11:36.835
- Kenai.
- Sitka, no, you gotta get out of here.

162
00:11:36.907 --> 00:11:38.706
- What?
- The bear. Behind you.

163
00:11:41.985 --> 00:11:44.145
Hey, bear, come on. Over here.

164
00:11:44.504 --> 00:11:46.423
Come on, bear, come this way.

165
00:11:59.620 --> 00:12:00.744
Denahi!

166
00:12:01.779 --> 00:12:04.866
- Hold on.
- Pull.

167
00:12:34.211 --> 00:12:36.371
Sitka. Sitka!

168
00:13:00.403 --> 00:13:01.527
Sitka.

169
00:13:13.280 --> 00:13:15.123
Come on!

170
00:13:18.678 --> 00:13:20.685
- Sitka!
- Sitka!

171
00:13:22.597 --> 00:13:24.601
Sitka. Sitka!

172
00:13:24.636 --> 00:13:27.320
- Sitka?
- Sitka, where are you?

173
00:13:28.315 --> 00:13:29.275
Kenai.

174
00:13:40.112 --> 00:13:41.312
No.

175
00:13:42.711 --> 00:13:44.358
Sitka!

176
00:13:46.110 --> 00:13:47.593
Sitka!

177
00:13:49.549 --> 00:13:51.669
Denahi, let's find him!

178
00:13:51.704 --> 00:13:52.957
Sitka.

179
00:13:54.028 --> 00:13:56.634
Sitka, where are you? Sitka!

180
00:14:56.570 --> 00:14:59.374
- You ready?
- For what?

181
00:14:59.449 --> 00:15:01.369
For going after the bear.

182
00:15:02.889 --> 00:15:06.816
I know what you're feeling,
but killing that bear is wrong.

183
00:15:07.247 --> 00:15:10.574
Wrong? Our brother is dead
and it's because of that monster.

184
00:15:10.966 --> 00:15:13.410
I don't blame the bear, Kenai.

185
00:15:18.005 --> 00:15:21.124
- I see.
- Killing the bear won't make you a man.

186
00:15:21.204 --> 00:15:22.488
Now you're trying to be wise.

187
00:15:22.523 --> 00:15:25.207
I'm trying to follow my totem.
Why can't you?

188
00:15:25.283 --> 00:15:28.282
You really think love
has anything to do with being a man?

189
00:15:28.317 --> 00:15:31.205
A man wouldn't just sit here
and do nothing.

190
00:15:31.721 --> 00:15:35.244
Kenai. Don't upset the spirits.

191
00:15:35.759 --> 00:15:39.043
Spirits.
Thanks for your wisdom.

192
00:16:03.432 --> 00:16:04.992
I've got to stop him.

193
00:16:13.030 --> 00:16:15.393
You left too soon, Sitka.

194
00:16:15.428 --> 00:16:17.915
Your brothers need your guidance.

195
00:17:15.972 --> 00:17:18.219
Ha!

196
00:18:48.985 --> 00:18:50.109
Kenai.

197
00:19:49.449 --> 00:19:50.572
What?

198
00:21:01.029 --> 00:21:02.229
Sitka.

199
00:21:58.373 --> 00:21:59.540
No.

200
00:22:52.757 --> 00:22:54.961
<i>I don't blame the bear, Kenai.</i>

201
00:22:58.196 --> 00:23:01.119
<i>A man wouldn't just sit here
and do nothing.</i>

202
00:23:49.901 --> 00:23:54.025
So, Kenai,
you've decided to join the living.

203
00:23:54.261 --> 00:23:56.464
Ooh-hoo.
That's quite a bump you've got.

204
00:23:56.540 --> 00:23:59.343
That must have been one heck of a ride
down the rapids.

205
00:23:59.659 --> 00:24:00.782
Tanana?

206
00:24:03.498 --> 00:24:05.985
Ooh.

207
00:24:06.257 --> 00:24:07.941
Nana, you won't believe this.

208
00:24:07.976 --> 00:24:10.343
I was at the top of this rock,
and all of a sudden...

209
00:24:13.855 --> 00:24:15.895
Kenai, honey. Shh-shh-shh.

210
00:24:16.174 --> 00:24:17.941
I don't speak bear.

211
00:24:23.372 --> 00:24:24.572
No.

212
00:24:25.411 --> 00:24:29.099
No, no! No!

213
00:24:32.010 --> 00:24:36.133
All right! All right! All right!
Would you settle down? Settle!

214
00:24:36.209 --> 00:24:39.132
Kenai! Kenai...

215
00:24:39.208 --> 00:24:43.015
Kenai. Kenai. This isn't going to work.

216
00:24:46.006 --> 00:24:49.606
Kenai, listen to me. Sitka did this.

217
00:24:51.444 --> 00:24:55.448
Strange. Spirits don't usually
make these kind of changes.

218
00:24:55.803 --> 00:24:58.287
Oh. Oh, my, my, my, my.

219
00:24:58.322 --> 00:25:01.409
Sitka must have something really big
planned for you. Yep, yep.

220
00:25:01.481 --> 00:25:04.045
You are going to get
a whole new perspective on things.

221
00:25:04.200 --> 00:25:08.404
Oh! Do you see
in black and white or colour?

222
00:25:08.439 --> 00:25:11.883
Hey. Listen to me.
You got yourself into this mess.

223
00:25:11.918 --> 00:25:15.126
If you want to change,
take it up with your brother's spirit.

224
00:25:17.197 --> 00:25:21.277
You'll find him on the mountain
where the lights touch the earth.

225
00:25:21.356 --> 00:25:23.919
He'll help you make up
for what you've done wrong.

226
00:25:23.995 --> 00:25:26.635
But I didn't do anything wrong.

227
00:25:27.274 --> 00:25:29.434
Tanana? Tanana!

228
00:25:29.514 --> 00:25:32.317
Wait. I didn't do anything wrong.

229
00:25:33.392 --> 00:25:35.952
- I don't even know how to get there.
- What happened to them?

230
00:25:35.987 --> 00:25:37.032
I don't know.

231
00:25:37.111 --> 00:25:39.150
They were here.
Now they're gone.

232
00:25:39.185 --> 00:25:41.070
Yeah, that's pretty weird.

233
00:25:41.510 --> 00:25:45.197
So you're telling me you didn't eat them
and you have no idea where they are?

234
00:25:45.429 --> 00:25:48.748
- Uh-uh.
- Hey, hey, you. You just talked.

235
00:25:48.783 --> 00:25:51.835
Just back away, real slow-like.

236
00:25:51.907 --> 00:25:55.430
- How did you do that?
- I knew you had them.

237
00:25:56.546 --> 00:25:57.790
Are we there yet?

238
00:25:57.825 --> 00:26:00.465
Don't make me
turn this formation around.

239
00:26:01.664 --> 00:26:05.744
Hey. Wait. Come back.
I'm trying to find where the lights...

240
00:26:05.824 --> 00:26:10.264
- What's he getting worked up about?
- Maybe the goose pooped on him, eh?

241
00:26:12.061 --> 00:26:14.384
Oh, gee. He's looking over here.
Let's beat it. This way.

242
00:26:14.461 --> 00:26:17.429
- No, this way.
- Thank you very much.

243
00:26:17.500 --> 00:26:19.900
- Just stay still and...
- Hey, you two!

244
00:26:19.980 --> 00:26:21.984
Head down.

245
00:26:22.019 --> 00:26:23.904
I think he's seen us. Now what?

246
00:26:23.939 --> 00:26:26.622
- Act like we're not here.
- We're not here.

247
00:26:26.778 --> 00:26:28.897
- Shh! What are you doing?
- You said to...

248
00:26:28.932 --> 00:26:30.581
- Don't say anything. Shh!
- Okay.

249
00:26:30.616 --> 00:26:31.904
- I said, "Don't say anything."
- Um, excuse me.

250
00:26:33.416 --> 00:26:36.296
- Don't eat us.
- You won't like us, eh? We're gamey.

251
00:26:36.375 --> 00:26:38.294
Yeah. Eat hoof-for-brains over there.

252
00:26:38.375 --> 00:26:40.894
- Pine-cone breath.
- Crusty tail.

253
00:26:40.929 --> 00:26:42.301
- Twig legs.
- Big nose.

254
00:26:43.373 --> 00:26:45.652
- Sorry.
- You went too far that time.

255
00:26:45.687 --> 00:26:47.496
- Okay, I'm sorry.
- Guys.

256
00:26:47.571 --> 00:26:50.779
- Yours is bigger than mine.
- I'm not eating anybody.

257
00:26:50.891 --> 00:26:52.495
Oh, whew.

258
00:26:52.690 --> 00:26:55.297
- That's mighty decent of you, eh.
- My name's Rutt.

259
00:26:55.370 --> 00:26:57.498
- This is my brother Tuke.
- How's it going, Bear?

260
00:26:57.889 --> 00:27:01.936
- Don't call me that.
- Sorry, uh...

261
00:27:02.208 --> 00:27:05.851
- Mr. Bear?
- I mean, I'm not a bear. I hate bears.

262
00:27:05.927 --> 00:27:09.810
- Well, gee, you're one big beaver.
- No kidding, eh?

263
00:27:10.166 --> 00:27:12.849
Do either of you know
where the lights touch the earth?

264
00:27:13.165 --> 00:27:15.685
Yee... ahh...

265
00:27:16.044 --> 00:27:19.408
No. Uh, no. Sorry, bear... Er, beaver.

266
00:27:19.443 --> 00:27:22.962
I'm not a beaver, I'm a bear...
No, I mean, I'm not a bear.

267
00:27:22.997 --> 00:27:25.359
- I'm a man.
- Excuse me.

268
00:27:25.394 --> 00:27:27.686
I was transformed into a bear.

269
00:27:27.721 --> 00:27:31.280
Magically. I was lifted into the sky
by my brother.

270
00:27:31.315 --> 00:27:32.687
Uh-huh.

271
00:27:33.159 --> 00:27:34.919
- Crazy.
- Gesundheit.

272
00:27:34.954 --> 00:27:36.926
No. Fruitcake.

273
00:27:36.998 --> 00:27:39.802
- Are you okay?
- No. That bear. Over there.

274
00:27:39.877 --> 00:27:42.005
- He's crazy.
- I am not crazy.

275
00:27:42.876 --> 00:27:45.199
Whoever said you were?
We understand.

276
00:27:45.276 --> 00:27:47.375
- You do?
- Oh, yeah, yeah.

277
00:27:47.410 --> 00:27:49.475
You see, we're not moose either.

278
00:27:49.510 --> 00:27:50.915
- We're not?
- No.

279
00:27:51.474 --> 00:27:54.234
We're like, uh...
We're like squirrels. Yeah.

280
00:27:54.314 --> 00:27:56.920
Oh. Oh, yeah. Beauty, eh?

281
00:27:56.992 --> 00:28:01.631
Well, he's actually the squirrel.
I'm more of a purebred wolverine.

282
00:28:01.666 --> 00:28:03.758
Look at these cuspids.

283
00:28:04.191 --> 00:28:08.030
- Give him a little room.
- Why am I talking to moose?

284
00:28:08.065 --> 00:28:10.474
- No, we're squirrels, eh.
- Wolverine.

285
00:28:11.548 --> 00:28:13.468
I'll find it myself.

286
00:28:14.348 --> 00:28:16.748
- Oh, I wouldn't go that way.
- Why not, eh?

287
00:28:17.106 --> 00:28:19.713
Uh, well, there was a reason.

288
00:28:19.786 --> 00:28:22.034
- You brought it up.
- I'm trying to...

289
00:28:24.265 --> 00:28:26.064
Ow!

290
00:28:28.783 --> 00:28:29.984
Ow!

291
00:28:30.063 --> 00:28:33.631
- So, you think of it yet?
- Well, no, but it's driving me nuts.

292
00:28:34.022 --> 00:28:35.822
Ow.

293
00:28:48.658 --> 00:28:50.577
Hey. Is the coast clear?

294
00:28:50.658 --> 00:28:53.297
- What?
- Are there any hunters around?

295
00:28:53.456 --> 00:28:55.704
- Uh... No.
- Oh, good!

296
00:28:55.776 --> 00:28:58.380
You didn't see the trap?

297
00:28:58.415 --> 00:29:02.298
I saw it from a mile away.
You must be pretty embarrassed.

298
00:29:02.374 --> 00:29:03.574
Don't worry.

299
00:29:04.573 --> 00:29:06.896
I won't tell anyone.

300
00:29:07.133 --> 00:29:09.381
- What?
- You need to get down. Let me help.

301
00:29:09.453 --> 00:29:10.980
Oh, wait. Ow!

302
00:29:11.052 --> 00:29:13.539
- Hold still.
- Just... Stop that. Ow!

303
00:29:14.211 --> 00:29:15.618
If you just...

304
00:29:16.011 --> 00:29:18.454
- Stop it!
- It's no use.

305
00:29:18.809 --> 00:29:23.013
The only way to get down
is to chew your own foot off.

306
00:29:23.048 --> 00:29:26.855
I don't need some stupid bear's help.
I just need the stick.

307
00:29:26.927 --> 00:29:29.130
- Okay, here.
- No, I'll do it myself.

308
00:29:29.207 --> 00:29:31.694
Put it back. No, where you found it.

309
00:29:31.846 --> 00:29:34.565
- Oh.
- To the left. By the little rock.

310
00:29:34.600 --> 00:29:35.928
- Here?
- Yes.

311
00:29:36.005 --> 00:29:37.325
Okay.

312
00:29:38.404 --> 00:29:40.929
Boy, that tree is strong, huh?

313
00:29:40.964 --> 00:29:43.931
You know, when I was little,
I was really into climbing trees.

314
00:29:44.003 --> 00:29:45.203
All kinds of trees.

315
00:29:45.282 --> 00:29:50.802
I climbed pine trees, oaks, cedars,
maples, birch trees, willow trees...

316
00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:52.925
My eyes were watering
and my tongue was swollen.

317
00:29:52.960 --> 00:29:56.483
From that moment on,
I was more careful about what I lick.

318
00:30:00.638 --> 00:30:05.885
Ha! See? It's all about using your head.

319
00:30:08.036 --> 00:30:11.559
That was funny. Do it again.

320
00:30:11.635 --> 00:30:15.158
- Don't you have someplace to go?
- Yeah, the salmon run.

321
00:30:16.914 --> 00:30:20.152
How about this?
I get you down, then we go together.

322
00:30:20.187 --> 00:30:23.033
- Deal?
- Yeah, okay, fine.

323
00:30:23.111 --> 00:30:26.395
If you can magically get me down,
I'll go with you to this...

324
00:30:26.471 --> 00:30:29.394
- Salmon run.
- Whatever. But if you can't...

325
00:30:29.670 --> 00:30:33.597
You turn around, walk away,
and never come back, ever.

326
00:30:33.668 --> 00:30:35.353
- You swear?
- Yeah.

327
00:30:35.388 --> 00:30:38.236
- Pinky swear?
- Yeah, sure, fine, pinky swear.

328
00:30:38.308 --> 00:30:41.111
But this is a human trap
and you're just a dumb little bear.

329
00:30:41.187 --> 00:30:43.195
There's no way
you're going to be able...

330
00:30:48.624 --> 00:30:51.428
Okay, so I'm thinking
we travel by day and sleep by night.

331
00:30:51.503 --> 00:30:54.230
My bedtime is an hour after sunset...

332
00:30:56.302 --> 00:30:57.590
Run!

333
00:30:58.061 --> 00:30:59.785
Yeah, good riddance.

334
00:31:14.177 --> 00:31:15.502
Denahi.

335
00:31:15.537 --> 00:31:16.944
Denahi, you found me.

336
00:31:18.816 --> 00:31:20.583
You wouldn't believe
what a nightmare this has been.

337
00:31:22.215 --> 00:31:24.462
Denahi? It's me. Kenai.

338
00:31:56.246 --> 00:31:58.010
Is he gone?

339
00:31:58.045 --> 00:31:59.812
- I think he was going...
- Shh!

340
00:32:07.683 --> 00:32:09.723
Hello. I can't breathe.

341
00:32:23.878 --> 00:32:26.878
- Why is he chasing me?
- That's what they do.

342
00:32:26.957 --> 00:32:30.525
- But it's not like him.
- Lucky for him, he didn't find us

343
00:32:30.596 --> 00:32:33.280
'cause when I get in a fight,
I go all crazy

344
00:32:33.355 --> 00:32:35.722
and I'm a raging ball of brown fur.

345
00:32:36.674 --> 00:32:40.481
I mean, I don't want to brag or nothing,
but I got some moves.

346
00:32:40.913 --> 00:32:44.240
- Oh, really?
- Yep. This first one, well...

347
00:32:44.792 --> 00:32:48.735
It's just a little thing
I like to call "The Slasher."

348
00:32:48.770 --> 00:32:52.679
And this one I like to call
"Flying Fury of Death."

349
00:32:52.949 --> 00:32:56.113
- Uh-huh. He's coming back.
- Where?

350
00:32:56.668 --> 00:32:58.752
Typical.

351
00:32:58.828 --> 00:33:01.948
Yeah, well,
the next time we run into that hunter...

352
00:33:02.027 --> 00:33:05.550
There is no "we."
I'm not taking you to any salmon run.

353
00:33:05.746 --> 00:33:08.113
What? But you pinky swore.

354
00:33:08.185 --> 00:33:09.865
Yeah, well, things change.

355
00:33:10.665 --> 00:33:12.105
See you, kid.

356
00:33:13.704 --> 00:33:14.751
Wait, uh...

357
00:33:18.223 --> 00:33:21.901
The truth is,
I got separated from my mom.

358
00:33:21.936 --> 00:33:24.546
And now, with this hunter around...

359
00:33:24.581 --> 00:33:28.508
- Kid, I got my own problems.
- Come on. Please.

360
00:33:28.580 --> 00:33:32.300
Can't we just go together?
There's a lot of bears and a ton of fish,

361
00:33:32.379 --> 00:33:35.859
and every night we watch the lights
touch the mountain. Last year...

362
00:33:35.938 --> 00:33:38.857
- Wait, wait. What did you say?
- Lots of bears and fish.

363
00:33:38.892 --> 00:33:41.137
No. You know
where the lights touch the earth?

364
00:33:41.216 --> 00:33:44.060
Yeah! The top of the mountain
right by the salmon run.

365
00:33:44.095 --> 00:33:47.499
- You're kidding me.
- No, no, they're practically next door.

366
00:33:47.574 --> 00:33:49.854
Come on, I'll show you. It'll be great.

367
00:33:50.853 --> 00:33:54.257
I promise to help you escape
from every trap you walk into.

368
00:33:54.333 --> 00:33:55.980
I'm not going to walk into any more...

369
00:33:56.532 --> 00:34:01.256
- Traps.
- Come on. What do you say?

370
00:34:02.970 --> 00:34:05.529
Sure you can take me
to where the lights touch the earth?

371
00:34:05.564 --> 00:34:07.296
Yeah, no problem.

372
00:34:12.688 --> 00:34:15.731
- If you slow me down...
- I won't, I promise.

373
00:34:16.806 --> 00:34:19.206
All right, we leave first thing tomorrow.

374
00:34:32.082 --> 00:34:34.961
And keep all that cuddly bear stuff
to a minimum, okay, kid?

375
00:34:34.996 --> 00:34:37.808
My name's not "kid." It's Koda.

376
00:34:45.318 --> 00:34:46.878
What's your name?

377
00:34:52.516 --> 00:34:54.163
- Good day.
- How's it going, eh?

378
00:34:54.236 --> 00:34:58.403
Beauty. So we got a lot to get done
today. You want to get started?

379
00:34:58.475 --> 00:35:00.394
- Yeah. Just give me one sec, eh?
- Okay.

380
00:35:01.594 --> 00:35:03.754
Woo-oo-hoo...

381
00:35:04.033 --> 00:35:06.040
- Just help me crack this.
- All right.

382
00:35:06.193 --> 00:35:07.557
Ah.

383
00:35:07.592 --> 00:35:09.839
- You ready now?
- Almost.

384
00:35:11.591 --> 00:35:14.035
Just want to do "dog facing forward."

385
00:35:14.271 --> 00:35:17.990
- Oh, come on.
- Good. Okay.

386
00:35:18.025 --> 00:35:19.550
And go.

387
00:35:21.549 --> 00:35:23.073
This a nice patch here.

388
00:35:23.108 --> 00:35:26.467
Don't go near this patch here.
Something went here.

389
00:35:47.501 --> 00:35:48.788
Ahh!

390
00:36:05.336 --> 00:36:08.020
Skinny. Fat. Skinny. Fat.

391
00:36:08.055 --> 00:36:10.935
Hey, I've got a mountain to get to.
Come on, kid.

392
00:36:11.175 --> 00:36:14.339
I told you before. My name's Koda.

393
00:36:14.413 --> 00:36:17.298
Say it with me. Ko... Da.

394
00:36:17.333 --> 00:36:20.213
Sure your mom didn't ditch you,
Ko-duh?

395
00:36:21.012 --> 00:36:22.452
Humph.

396
00:36:28.369 --> 00:36:31.096
- Rutt.
- Go away, eh, I'm eating twigs.

397
00:36:31.329 --> 00:36:34.296
- Rutt.
- You're breaking my concentration.

398
00:36:34.368 --> 00:36:37.008
We should start running, like now!

399
00:36:37.087 --> 00:36:41.331
I can't. I'm still digesting, eh.
I'll get cramps.

400
00:36:46.924 --> 00:36:50.251
- Whoa, gee! He's after us!
- Come on, little brother.

401
00:36:51.243 --> 00:36:52.683
Cramp!

402
00:36:53.643 --> 00:36:57.482
If you really want to know
how me and my mom got separated...

403
00:36:57.517 --> 00:37:01.321
I was saving this story
for the salmon run, but I'll tell you.

404
00:37:02.760 --> 00:37:07.407
It was probably the fifth or sixth
most coldest day in my entire life.

405
00:37:07.479 --> 00:37:10.446
- Sounds good. You should save it.
- You think so?

406
00:37:10.518 --> 00:37:12.841
- Oh, yeah. For your friends.
- Oh.

407
00:37:13.477 --> 00:37:15.876
- Well, I have this other story.
- Tell you what.

408
00:37:16.196 --> 00:37:18.956
- How about no talking?
- Okay.

409
00:37:19.555 --> 00:37:21.714
- Then I'll sing.
- No, no, no.

410
00:37:21.749 --> 00:37:23.874
<i>Tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

411
00:37:23.909 --> 00:37:25.194
Will you stop it?

412
00:37:25.273 --> 00:37:27.273
<i>New friends and new places to see</i>

413
00:37:27.308 --> 00:37:29.450
Come on, quit it. Shh!

414
00:37:29.485 --> 00:37:31.738
Koda, stop singing.

415
00:37:31.773 --> 00:37:33.992
<i>Yes, I'm on my way</i>

416
00:37:34.071 --> 00:37:38.271
<i>And there's nowhere else
that I'd rather be</i>

417
00:37:39.430 --> 00:37:43.193
<i>Tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

418
00:37:43.228 --> 00:37:46.916
<i>And I'm loving every step I take</i>

419
00:37:47.548 --> 00:37:51.714
<i>With the sun beating down
Yes, I'm on my way</i>

420
00:37:52.226 --> 00:37:56.034
<i>And I can't keep this smile off my face</i>

421
00:37:56.585 --> 00:38:01.025
<i>'Cause there's nothing like
seeing each other again</i>

422
00:38:01.343 --> 00:38:04.911
<i>No matter what the distance between</i>

423
00:38:05.742 --> 00:38:12.069
<i>And the stories that we tell
will make you smile</i>

424
00:38:12.381 --> 00:38:15.948
<i>Oh, it really lifts my heart</i>

425
00:38:16.019 --> 00:38:19.379
<i>So tell them all I'm on my way</i>

426
00:38:19.458 --> 00:38:23.582
<i>New friends and new places to see</i>

427
00:38:23.657 --> 00:38:28.381
<i>And to sleep under the stars
Who could ask for more?</i>

428
00:38:28.456 --> 00:38:31.859
<i>With the moon keeping watch over me</i>

429
00:38:32.615 --> 00:38:37.493
<i>Not the snow, not the rain
can change my mind</i>

430
00:38:37.528 --> 00:38:41.617
<i>The sun will come out, wait and see</i>

431
00:38:41.652 --> 00:38:45.295
<i>And the feeling of the wind in your face</i>

432
00:38:45.371 --> 00:38:48.975
<i>Can lift your heart, whoa</i>

433
00:38:49.010 --> 00:38:51.977
<i>There's nowhere I would rather be</i>

434
00:38:54.368 --> 00:38:56.975
<i>'Cause I'm on my way now</i>

435
00:38:59.128 --> 00:39:01.331
<i>Well and true</i>

436
00:39:03.686 --> 00:39:05.889
<i>I'm on my way now</i>

437
00:39:07.045 --> 00:39:09.293
Hey, hold on, eh?

438
00:39:09.365 --> 00:39:10.444
Wait up.

439
00:39:12.724 --> 00:39:15.423
- How's it going, bear boy?
- And, uh, smallish bear.

440
00:39:15.458 --> 00:39:18.123
I didn't know you had a little brother.
He's cute.

441
00:39:18.203 --> 00:39:21.966
- Actually, he's...
- There was this hunter following us.

442
00:39:22.041 --> 00:39:25.160
We was thinking if we could
maybe just hang out with you guys.

443
00:39:25.195 --> 00:39:27.680
- Just hang out.
- Yeah, it'd be fun.

444
00:39:27.760 --> 00:39:30.879
- If the hunter was going to catch up...
- Then you'd eat him.

445
00:39:30.959 --> 00:39:34.406
- That's what we was thinking.
- We lost the hunter at the glacier.

446
00:39:34.478 --> 00:39:36.277
You don't think he'll follow those?

447
00:39:36.837 --> 00:39:40.884
- They are quite nice.
- I've got an idea.

448
00:39:40.956 --> 00:39:43.236
Okay, this is really weird.

449
00:39:44.475 --> 00:39:47.518
- I'm driving.
- When can I have a turn?

450
00:39:47.553 --> 00:39:50.553
It's not as easy as it looks.
Just watch what I do.

451
00:39:50.633 --> 00:39:54.080
Let's get a back seat or something.
I look like you hunted me.

452
00:39:54.712 --> 00:39:57.635
<i>Tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

453
00:39:57.711 --> 00:39:58.954
Hey, come on.

454
00:39:59.031 --> 00:40:01.791
<i>And I just can't wait to be there</i>

455
00:40:03.509 --> 00:40:07.349
<i>Blue skies ahead
Yes, I'm on my way</i>

456
00:40:07.948 --> 00:40:12.235
<i>Nothing but good times to share</i>

457
00:40:12.307 --> 00:40:15.831
<i>So tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

458
00:40:16.706 --> 00:40:19.826
<i>And I just can't wait to be home</i>

459
00:40:21.225 --> 00:40:25.348
<i>With the sun beating down
Yes, I'm on my way</i>

460
00:40:25.903 --> 00:40:29.742
<i>With nothing but good times to show</i>

461
00:40:29.777 --> 00:40:33.026
<i>I'm on my way</i>

462
00:40:33.101 --> 00:40:36.744
<i>Yes, I'm on my way</i>

463
00:40:37.780 --> 00:40:39.187
Beauty, eh?

464
00:40:40.459 --> 00:40:43.978
Okay, here's how I remember it.
The snow is white, it's all right.

465
00:40:44.013 --> 00:40:46.377
Yellow or green, it's just not clean.

466
00:40:46.412 --> 00:40:47.981
I learned that one the hard way.

467
00:40:48.296 --> 00:40:52.463
That reminds me. Last year at the
salmon run my friend Bucky dared me.

468
00:40:52.536 --> 00:40:55.535
But I'd heard of a cub
who stuck his tongue to an iceberg.

469
00:40:55.570 --> 00:40:57.379
Then he started to float away.

470
00:40:57.414 --> 00:41:00.139
To save him
they had to rip off his tongue,

471
00:41:00.174 --> 00:41:03.021
so now he hath to talk like thith
all the time and...

472
00:41:03.093 --> 00:41:05.820
- Do you ever stop talking?
- Oh!

473
00:41:05.892 --> 00:41:08.296
Look. The night rainbow.

474
00:41:08.331 --> 00:41:12.291
- You can see the spirits from here.
- You know about the great spirits?

475
00:41:12.370 --> 00:41:15.490
