- This has got to be it.

721
00:59:15.122 --> 00:59:18.746
- Here you go, Koda.
- You gotta tell it, Kenai.

722
00:59:18.781 --> 00:59:21.790
- What?
- Yes. You caught it, you tell it.

723
00:59:21.865 --> 00:59:23.665
Didn't you play when you were a cub?

724
00:59:23.906 --> 00:59:25.989
- Um...
- Come on, Keno.

725
00:59:28.784 --> 00:59:30.628
Okay, all right already. All right.

726
00:59:31.263 --> 00:59:33.586
- You want to know what I did this year?
- Yes.

727
00:59:33.662 --> 00:59:38.549
I went on the longest, hardest, most
exhausting journey I've ever been on

728
00:59:38.621 --> 00:59:41.905
with the biggest pain in the neck
I've ever met.

729
00:59:43.740 --> 00:59:46.063
What do you expect
from a little brother?

730
00:59:48.178 --> 00:59:50.097
Okay, buddy, your turn.

731
00:59:50.738 --> 00:59:53.618
- Let's hear it, Koda.
- Okay, okay, here we go.

732
00:59:55.137 --> 00:59:57.896
This year I watched my mom
in a life-and-death struggle

733
00:59:57.931 --> 01:00:00.654
battling the most fiercest creature ever.

734
01:00:00.689 --> 01:00:02.258
- Who's next?
- What?

735
01:00:02.334 --> 01:00:06.893
Wait a minute. I think we all want
to hear the rest of that one, Koda.

736
01:00:06.928 --> 01:00:10.417
I thought you might say that.
Hmm... Let's see.

737
01:00:10.492 --> 01:00:14.856
It was probably the fifth or sixth
most coldest day in my entire life.

738
01:00:14.931 --> 01:00:17.898
Me and Mom were eating fish,
having a great time.

739
01:00:17.970 --> 01:00:22.737
All of a sudden she pushes me into
the bushes and tells me to be real quiet.

740
01:00:23.089 --> 01:00:26.492
She says, "I smell something."
So I started sniffing.

741
01:00:27.488 --> 01:00:30.051
There's something in the woods
running towards us,

742
01:00:30.127 --> 01:00:32.527
getting closer and closer.

743
01:00:34.206 --> 01:00:38.089
And then, out of the trees,
jumps a hunter.

744
01:00:39.844 --> 01:00:42.648
And now there's nowhere for Mom to go.

745
01:00:42.683 --> 01:00:46.283
The monster has her backed up
against this giant glacier.

746
01:00:50.521 --> 01:00:54.045
The monster attacks,
but Mom's too quick for him.

747
01:00:54.080 --> 01:00:59.447
And before he can do it again, she
stands up real big and yells, "Go away."

748
01:00:59.518 --> 01:01:01.318
<i>Kenai.</i>

749
01:01:01.398 --> 01:01:03.077
Mom smells more of them.

750
01:01:03.158 --> 01:01:05.077
There's a whole pack
coming right at us.

751
01:01:05.557 --> 01:01:07.476
Sitka, no. The bear. Behind you.

752
01:01:07.557 --> 01:01:09.804
<i>She runs to stop them
before they get to me.</i>

753
01:01:09.876 --> 01:01:12.799
<i>They're all around her,
poking her with sticks.</i>

754
01:01:12.875 --> 01:01:16.518
<i>- Sitka.
- The whole thing broke and fell off.</i>

755
01:01:16.594 --> 01:01:18.361
<i>There was ice everywhere.</i>

756
01:01:18.433 --> 01:01:21.037
<i>She couldn't hold her breath
any longer, and pow.</i>

757
01:01:21.072 --> 01:01:24.912
She bursts out of the water.
I've never been so scared in my life.

758
01:01:25.191 --> 01:01:27.995
<i>- I'm going after the bear.
- Koda?</i>

759
01:01:28.071 --> 01:01:29.910
<i>- Sitka wouldn't want it.
- Sitka's not here</i>

760
01:01:29.945 --> 01:01:31.917
<i>because of that monster.</i>

761
01:01:33.989 --> 01:01:37.428
Whoa. Fell off a glacier?
I've never seen anything like that.

762
01:01:37.463 --> 01:01:39.468
Can you imagine?

763
01:01:40.107 --> 01:01:42.671
Kenai. What's the matter, Kenai?

764
01:01:42.747 --> 01:01:45.266
- What happened next?
- Was she okay?

765
01:01:46.346 --> 01:01:49.585
Hey, Kenai, what's wrong?
Where you going?

766
01:01:49.664 --> 01:01:52.784
She got out of the water okay.
That's how we got separated.

767
01:01:52.819 --> 01:01:55.663
Right after that I met Kenai.

768
01:01:55.698 --> 01:01:56.787
Kenai?

769
01:02:39.811 --> 01:02:43.291
Scared you again, huh?

770
01:02:43.370 --> 01:02:45.089
- Yeah.
- Where have you been?

771
01:02:45.124 --> 01:02:46.774
- You look horrible.
- Koda...

772
01:02:46.809 --> 01:02:49.689
My mom says when
you eat too much fish, just lie down.

773
01:02:52.007 --> 01:02:53.927
There's something I, uh...

774
01:02:54.887 --> 01:02:56.970
You know that story
you told me last night?

775
01:02:57.046 --> 01:03:00.245
- Yeah.
- Well, I have a story to tell you.

776
01:03:00.280 --> 01:03:02.489
Really? What's it about?

777
01:03:02.524 --> 01:03:05.567
Well, it's kind of about a man,

778
01:03:05.643 --> 01:03:08.130
and kind of about a bear.

779
01:03:08.203 --> 01:03:11.126
But mostly it's about a monster.

780
01:03:12.401 --> 01:03:15.460
A monster who did something so bad...

781
01:03:15.495 --> 01:03:18.520
<i>Everywhere I turn I hurt someone</i>

782
01:03:19.759 --> 01:03:25.203
<i>But there's nothing I can say
to change the things I've done</i>

783
01:03:26.317 --> 01:03:29.721
<i>I'd do anything within my power</i>

784
01:03:29.796 --> 01:03:32.796
<i>I'd give everything I've got</i>

785
01:03:32.876 --> 01:03:37.283
<i>But the path I seek
is hidden from me now</i>

786
01:03:37.354 --> 01:03:40.442
Koda, I did something very wrong.

787
01:03:40.514 --> 01:03:43.356
<i>Brother bear, I let you down</i>

788
01:03:43.391 --> 01:03:46.199
I don't like this story.

789
01:03:46.272 --> 01:03:51.111
<i>You trusted me, believed in me
and I let you down</i>

790
01:03:51.146 --> 01:03:52.715
Your mother's not coming.

791
01:03:52.790 --> 01:03:55.997
<i>Of all the things I hid from you</i>

792
01:03:56.069 --> 01:03:58.708
<i>I cannot hide the shame</i>

793
01:03:58.789 --> 01:03:59.948
<i>And I pray someone</i>

794
01:03:59.983 --> 01:04:01.033
No. No!

795
01:04:01.068 --> 01:04:06.151
<i>Something will come
to take away the pain</i>

796
01:04:06.826 --> 01:04:10.153
<i>There's no way out</i>

797
01:04:10.225 --> 01:04:13.345
<i>Of this dark place</i>

798
01:04:13.424 --> 01:04:16.828
<i>No, no future</i>

799
01:04:20.062 --> 01:04:25.190
<i>I know I can't be free</i>

800
01:04:27.301 --> 01:04:30.781
<i>But I can't see another way</i>

801
01:04:32.219 --> 01:04:36.866
<i>And I can't face another day</i>

802
01:04:39.497 --> 01:04:42.345
Koda? Koda?

803
01:04:44.296 --> 01:04:45.976
Koda!

804
01:04:50.014 --> 01:04:51.574
Koda, I wish I could...

805
01:04:52.654 --> 01:04:55.260
If there was just some way...

806
01:04:56.412 --> 01:04:57.895
I'd give anything if...

807
01:05:00.891 --> 01:05:03.291
If I could just...

808
01:05:14.608 --> 01:05:16.855
I'm sorry, Koda.

809
01:05:17.446 --> 01:05:19.094
I'm so sorry.

810
01:05:54.795 --> 01:05:56.715
I'm sorry, Kenai.

811
01:05:57.315 --> 01:05:59.399
I don't know what I'm doing any more.

812
01:06:00.395 --> 01:06:02.314
I need help.

813
01:06:15.910 --> 01:06:17.350
Sitka.

814
01:06:27.387 --> 01:06:29.272
Look, I am sorry.

815
01:06:29.307 --> 01:06:31.226
If I was driving
this never would have happened.

816
01:06:31.306 --> 01:06:36.433
- You never let me do nothing.
- Trample off. I said sorry. Let it go.

817
01:06:36.504 --> 01:06:38.709
I can't believe you totalled a mammoth.

818
01:06:38.744 --> 01:06:42.191
- That mountain came out of nowhere.
- I cannot accept your apology.

819
01:06:42.262 --> 01:06:45.863
- It was in my blind spot...
- Look. It's that little cub.

820
01:06:46.862 --> 01:06:49.785
- Gee, eh, something's bugging him.
- What's wrong, smallish bear?

821
01:06:50.181 --> 01:06:52.341
Nothing. I'm fine.

822
01:06:52.580 --> 01:06:57.618
Good. Where were we? Oh, yeah.
You're a big, selfish, reckless hoofer.

823
01:06:57.653 --> 01:06:59.626
- What?
- I'm fed up with it.

824
01:06:59.858 --> 01:07:03.217
- From now on, he's my new brother.
- You can't do that.

825
01:07:03.297 --> 01:07:06.775
Sorry, you've been replaced
with my dear brother...

826
01:07:06.810 --> 01:07:08.542
What's your name again?

827
01:07:08.615 --> 01:07:10.895
I don't want any more brothers.

828
01:07:10.975 --> 01:07:14.662
- See? He's had enough of you, too.
- I promise I'll change.

829
01:07:14.733 --> 01:07:18.333
Trample off. You won't.
Being a brother means nothing to you.

830
01:07:18.413 --> 01:07:20.617
- Of course it does.
- Like what?

831
01:07:20.652 --> 01:07:23.052
What about when your hooves
froze in the pond?

832
01:07:23.131 --> 01:07:26.491
- Who sat with you all winter, eh?
- You did.

833
01:07:26.570 --> 01:07:28.654
Who showed you
where the good grazing is?

834
01:07:28.729 --> 01:07:32.013
The really tender stuff
all covered in dew.

835
01:07:32.089 --> 01:07:34.653
Now, why do you think I did that, eh?

836
01:07:34.728 --> 01:07:36.613
Because I...

837
01:07:36.648 --> 01:07:39.451
Because I love... dew.

838
01:07:39.527 --> 01:07:42.854
Excuse me?
I don't believe I heard what you said.

839
01:07:42.966 --> 01:07:45.846
I said, "I love dew."

840
01:07:46.485 --> 01:07:48.732
I love dew, too, eh.

841
01:07:49.963 --> 01:07:52.328
Hey, I can change.

842
01:07:52.363 --> 01:07:55.647
- Go away, eh.
- Come on, I can change.

843
01:07:55.682 --> 01:07:59.283
- Go away, eh, don't touch me.
- I can change.

844
01:07:59.361 --> 01:08:01.041
Hey. No.

845
01:08:01.121 --> 01:08:03.084
Not there, that's the spot.

846
01:08:04.959 --> 01:08:06.684
Like, we'll see you later, smallish bear.

847
01:08:06.719 --> 01:08:10.482
Yeah, good day, eh.
You know what this calls for?

848
01:08:10.558 --> 01:08:14.757
A pile of delicious barley and amber
weed on a cool bed of malted hops.

849
01:08:14.837 --> 01:08:16.756
I like it.

850
01:08:32.552 --> 01:08:35.039
Sitka! Sitka, are you there?

851
01:08:36.231 --> 01:08:37.714
Sitka?

852
01:08:38.990 --> 01:08:43.034
Please. Please, Sitka.

853
01:08:43.069 --> 01:08:44.988
I don't know what else to do.

854
01:08:49.107 --> 01:08:50.308
Sitka.

855
01:08:56.945 --> 01:08:58.145
Denahi.

856
01:09:00.145 --> 01:09:02.064
Sitka, hurry, change me back.

857
01:09:13.900 --> 01:09:15.820
Where are you, Sitka?

858
01:09:37.893 --> 01:09:39.017
Denahi.

859
01:09:40.493 --> 01:09:42.053
Denahi, please.

860
01:09:46.371 --> 01:09:47.450
Koda.

861
01:09:58.128 --> 01:09:59.568
No!

862
01:10:01.567 --> 01:10:03.095
Leave him alone.

863
01:10:06.046 --> 01:10:07.366
Koda!

864
01:10:32.158 --> 01:10:33.718
Kenai?

865
01:10:50.234 --> 01:10:51.717
Sitka?

866
01:11:14.986 --> 01:11:19.307
Koda, don't be afraid. It's me.

867
01:12:05.012 --> 01:12:06.976
He needs me.

868
01:12:08.571 --> 01:12:11.931
You know, he did look better as a bear.

869
01:12:21.528 --> 01:12:24.615
But, Denahi...

870
01:12:25.286 --> 01:12:27.086
It's all right, Kenai.

871
01:12:34.524 --> 01:12:38.724
No matter what you choose,
you'll always be my little brother.

872
01:12:57.878 --> 01:12:59.166
Did I say little?

873
01:13:31.828 --> 01:13:33.388
Kenai.

874
01:13:58.621 --> 01:14:03.508
<i>My brother Kenai went on
to live with Koda and the other bears.</i>

875
01:14:03.579 --> 01:14:07.147
<i>He taught me
that love is very powerful.</i>

876
01:14:08.258 --> 01:14:11.825
<i>And I passed on the wisdom
of his story to our people.</i>

877
01:14:13.097 --> 01:14:16.064
<i>The story of a boy who became a man</i>

878
01:14:16.816 --> 01:14:18.779
<i>by becoming a bear.</i>

879
01:14:19.175 --> 01:14:22.174
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

880
01:14:22.209 --> 01:14:24.858
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

881
01:14:24.893 --> 01:14:29.780
<i>Fill our hearts and souls
with all you know</i>

882
01:14:30.212 --> 01:14:32.891
<i>Show us that in your eyes</i>

883
01:14:32.926 --> 01:14:35.535
<i>We are all the same</i>

884
01:14:35.570 --> 01:14:40.577
<i>Brothers to each other
in this world we remain</i>

885
01:14:40.649 --> 01:14:43.497
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

886
01:14:43.568 --> 01:14:48.335
<i>Brothers all the same</i>

887
01:15:00.164 --> 01:15:02.923
So, like, uh, what are you doing there,
smallish bear?

888
01:15:02.958 --> 01:15:05.482
I'm practising my moves.
Want to see one?

889
01:15:05.517 --> 01:15:07.969
Sure, eh.
This ought to be good, eh?

890
01:15:12.840 --> 01:15:16.723
Listen to me. I was a man
that was changed into a bear.

891
01:15:16.799 --> 01:15:20.082
No beaver. Man into bear. That's it.

892
01:15:20.158 --> 01:15:24.077
Oh. Yeah, so, before that
you was probably like a goat?

893
01:15:24.112 --> 01:15:26.281
- What about a water buffalo?
- No, he's a rabbit.

894
01:15:26.316 --> 01:15:29.675
Look at his ears and furry feet.
Watch out for the rabbit, eh.

895
01:15:29.710 --> 01:15:30.920
No way, eh.

896
01:15:30.955 --> 01:15:34.642
Okay, now, everyone,
take a big inhale, eh?

897
01:15:34.714 --> 01:15:36.122
And then on...

898
01:15:36.194 --> 01:15:40.241
On the exhale,
shift into salutation to the sun.

899
01:15:42.752 --> 01:15:48.119
No, you shut up.

900
01:15:56.788 --> 01:15:59.875
- How you doing over there, Koda?
- Oh, pretty good.

